<span id="freeTextContainer312254386937989632">I started this book 2 years ago and finally finished it. It was a chore, but one worth completing. I never really understood what happened in Hiroshima and Nagasaki. This is a beautiful and devastating reflection on that time. I can’t believe anything exists there now given the damage that was done. I will wonder what happened to Yasuko, although I can guess. Good book overall and a challenging read.</span>

