        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer169858475" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4928631826130211295">Historically, this is a very valuable book. As a story, it&apos;s only ok. It&apos;s mostly first-person accounts of the Hiroshima bombing, tied together with a storyline about a couple who are looking for a husband for their niece. They can&apos;t find anyone to marry her because suitors are concerned about radiation sickness. To fight the rumors and prove that his niece is healthy, the uncle writes a diary of the bombing. The descriptions are pretty graphic and the book is uncomfortable to read, but since th</span>
  <span id="freeText4928631826130211295" style="display:none">Historically, this is a very valuable book. As a story, it's only ok. It's mostly first-person accounts of the Hiroshima bombing, tied together with a storyline about a couple who are looking for a husband for their niece. They can't find anyone to marry her because suitors are concerned about radiation sickness. To fight the rumors and prove that his niece is healthy, the uncle writes a diary of the bombing. The descriptions are pretty graphic and the book is uncomfortable to read, but since the characters stay pretty flat and distant it's easier to get through.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4928631826130211295" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
