  <span id="freeText16463084802364289007" style="display:none">Upon finishing the book, I've become more enlightened on the horribly morbid effects of the atomic bombs dropped on Hiroshima and Nagasaki. The author really creates a submersible account of a man's life during such harsh times. Although somewhat slow and unexciting at times, the book was originally based off interviews given by victims of the event. Yet much careful and specific details are given to create many vivid moments to express such events. Overall, Ibuse shares with us an incredible story one of the world's most destructive events which greatly just how real the disasters were.</span>
